  "fragmentation_summary": "Państwowe Gospodarstwo Wodne Wody Polskie publishes nationally standardized Floods Directive hazard and risk maps through the ISOK Hydroportal. Products are organized by river basin and planning cycle but are available through a unified national interface. Surface-water (pluvial / powódź opadowa) hazard: no authoritative national or major-city product exists - the statutory ISOK/Wody Polskie Floods Directive maps explicitly exclude rainfall/stormwater flooding, and only academic case studies were found (verified June 2026).",
